#---: Phase 36: Maps \[COMPLETE\]

Implement maps. Maps are a reftype that are generic over the key types and the
value types. Open-addressing hash table with linear probing, tombstone
deletion, and automatic resizing at 2/3 load factor.

Completed substeps:

#ol:
  [#*: #+ map class definition in collections.z, alias in core.z]
  [#*: #+ type checker: _is_map_type, _map_key_type, _map_value_type helpers]
  [#*: #+ type checker: map synthesis in _monomorphize() — is_valtype=False,
  length, capacity, set, get (returns option), delete (returns bool), has
  (returns bool)]
  [#*: #+ type checker: skip generic class meta.create for map types]
  [#*: #+ emitter: _is_map_type, _map_key_type, _map_value_type helpers]
  [#*: #+ emitter: map type registration as class name]
  [#*: #+ emitter: _emit_mono_map() — bucket struct, map struct, hash function
  (splitmix64 for integers, FNV-1a for strings/str), key equality, destroy,
  create, grow/resize, find, set, get (option return), delete, has]
  [#*: #+ emitter: map construction interception (capacity argument)]
  [#*: #+ emitter: map method call interception (set, get, delete, has)]
  [#*: #+ emitter: statement-level map method calls with .take nullification]
  [#*: #+ emitter: .length and .capacity dotted path field access]
  [#*: #+ emitter: scope cleanup via _class_names / _emit_class_free]
  [#*: #+ Tests: 10 type checker tests, 14 emitter tests]
  [#*: #+ examples/maps.z demonstration program]
  [#*: #+ documentation: standardlibrary.pdoc, spec.pdoc, roadmap.pdoc]

Design decisions:

#ul:
  [#*: Open-addressing with linear probing (simpler than Python compact dict)]
  [#*: Insertion order NOT preserved (deferred to future optimization)]
  [#*: Hash: splitmix64 finalizer for integer keys, FNV-1a for string/str keys]
  [#*: Keys and values inline in buckets for valtypes, owned references for
  reftypes]
  [#*: get returns option (unlike list/array which return direct values)]
  [#*: Iteration deferred until iterators are implemented]

#---: Phase 37: v2 Integration Examples \[COMPLETE\]

Write comprehensive v2 example programs that exercise ownership, classes,
unions, protocols, generics and typedefs together. These serve as
integration tests for the full v2 feature set.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Write #~"examples/ownership.z": comprehensive ownership scenarios
    (take, borrow, lock, swap, scope cleanup, implicit take, standalone
    take-as-destroy) using classes with string fields.]
  [#*: #+ Write #~"examples/linkedlist.z": generic classes, nested class
    ownership, destruction chains, swap, and implicit take. Uses generic
    box class with multiple instantiations (i64, f64, string).]
  [#*: #+ Write #~"examples/result.z": non-generic #~"int_result" union
    (ok/err), generic system #~"option" with multiple monomorphizations
    (i64, f64), match expressions, ownership transfer.]
  [#*: #+ Write #~"examples/iterator.z": #~"provider" protocol with two
    implementations (#~"adder" record, #~"multiplier" record), dynamic
    dispatch, owned (#~"provider.create from: x.take") and borrowed
    (#~"provider.borrow from: x.lock") protocol instances.]
  [#*: #+ All v2 examples compile with gcc and produce correct output
    under ASan (address sanitizer). Zero leaks, zero errors.]

#---: Phase 38: SQL Compiler output \[COMPLETE\]

Have an alternate output format to create an sql file that will create tables
and dump details from the current compiler run into them with appropriate
indexes.

The sql format should be compatible with SQLite.

Output should include: VFS details (the files used to compile and the relative
structure parent/child). All tokens returned from the lexer, linked back to the
files they came from. The AST. The typechecker. The expected output. The
compiler needs to maintain or be able to generate lists of each of these
elements with numeric id's to allow references between them. The compiler may
need to be restructured to use formats friendly to sql dumping.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Add integer IDs to all compiler stages: #~"NodeID" on AST nodes,
    #~"TokenID" on lexer tokens, #~"TypeID" and #~"VariableID" on types,
    and file IDs from VFS. Add #~"CallKind" enum for call classification.]
  [#*: #+ Add #~"source_map" to C emitter (#~"TrackedList") linking each
    emitted C line back to its originating AST node ID.]
  [#*: #+ Implement #~"zsqldump.py" with #~"dump_sql()" generating
    SQLite-compatible SQL with 7 tables: #~"files", #~"tokens",
    #~"ast_nodes", #~"types", #~"type_children", #~"typed_nodes",
    #~"emitted_lines". Includes proper DDL, indexes, and foreign keys.]
  [#*: #+ Add #~"--dump-sql FILE" CLI flag to #~"zc.py" (supports file
    path or #~"-" for stdout).]
  [#*: #+ Add comprehensive tests in #~"test_findings.py": SQL generation,
    SQLite loading, table population for all 7 tables, foreign key
    integrity validation, and CLI integration test.]

