#---: Phase 42: if-as-expression and unit-level if \[COMPLETE\]

The spec defines #~"if" as both a statement and an expression, but only
the statement form was previously implemented. This phase adds
if-as-expression (42.1) and unit-level if for compile-time conditional
definitions (42.2). The spec is cleaned up to remove deprecated variable
binding syntax.

#----: 42.1 if-as-expression \[COMPLETE\]

When #~"if" has an #~"else" clause and is used in expression position
(e.g. RHS of an assignment, string interpolation), it evaluates to a
value. The #~"if" must be exhaustive and each arm must evaluate to the
same type, or must not complete (#~"return", #~"break", #~"continue").

Type checker (#~"src/ztypecheck.py"):

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Add #~"_last_statement_type()" helper to extract the type of
    the last expression in a #~"Statement" block]
  [#*: #+ Add #~"_NORETURN" sentinel for branches ending in
    #~"return"/#~"break"/#~"continue" (exempt from type matching)]
  [#*: #+ In #~"_check_if()", when the if node has an else clause,
    compute branch types and set #~"ifnode.type" to the common type]
  #*: #+ Report error when branch types are incompatible
  [#*: #+ Add #~"_check_exhaustive_if()" for exhaustiveness checking
    in all expression-consuming contexts (assignment, reassignment,
    string interpolation)]

Emitter (#~"src/zemitterc.py"):

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Add #~"_emit_branch_with_result()" helper that emits a
    branch body and assigns the last expression to a result variable]
  [#*: #+ Add #~"_emit_if_expression_value()" using temp-variable
    pattern: #~"Type _ifN; if (cond) { _ifN = val; } else { _ifN = val; }"]
  #*: #+ Wire up in #~"_emit_expression_value()" for #~"If" nodes
  #*: #+ Integrate with constant-condition folding from Phase 41
  #*: #+ Handle reftype ownership for string if-expressions

Tests:

#ol:
  #*: #+ Basic expression-if: #~"x: if 1 < 2 then 1 else 2"
  #*: #+ Max pattern: #~"x: if a > b then a else b"
  #*: #+ String expression-if: #~"s: if 1 < 2 then \"yes\" else \"no\""
  #*: #+ Multi-line branch: result is last expression in block
  #*: #+ Type mismatch error: #~"x: if 1 < 2 then 1 else \"hello\""
  #*: #+ Missing else error: #~"x: if 1 < 2 then 1" (not exhaustive)
  #*: #+ Exhaustiveness check in reassignment and interpolation
  #*: #+ Return exemption: branches ending in return/break/continue
  #*: #+ Constant-folded if-expression
