#----: 42.2 Unit-level if definition \[COMPLETE\]

Per the spec: an #~"if" may be used as a definition at the unit level.
Each clause must evaluate to a compile-time constant. Each arm may
produce a completely different type. This is compile-time conditional
compilation (similar to C's #~"#ifdef" but type-safe). Branch blocks
must use curly braces at unit level.

Type checker (#~"src/ztypecheck.py"):

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Add #~"_resolve_unit_level_if()" to handle #~"Expression(If)"
    in #~"_type_of_definition()"]
  [#*: #+ Enforce constant conditions: error if any condition lacks
    #~"const_value"]
  [#*: #+ Resolve type from the first true branch (different types per
    arm allowed)]
  #*: #+ Propagate #~"const_value" from taken branch to definition node

Tests:

#ol:
