#---: Phase 48b: Typed injected identifiers (return, break, continue) \[DONE\]

Replaced all string-based control flow detection with enum-based dispatch.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Added #~"ControlKind" enum to #~"ZType" (#~"RETURN", #~"BREAK",
    #~"CONTINUE", #~"ERROR") — set during type resolution of native functions
    in system.z.]
  [#*: #+ Added #~"CallKind.BREAK", #~"CallKind.CONTINUE", #~"CallKind.ERROR"
    to the #~"CallKind" enum. Type checker sets #~"call_kind" on Call nodes
    and propagates to Expression wrapper via #~"expr.call_kind".]
  [#*: #+ Emitter uses #~"call_kind" / #~"control_kind" for all control flow
    dispatch — no string matching on #~'"return"', #~'"break"', #~'"continue"'.]
  [#*: #+ Typedef method bodies are now type-checked. Operator lookup falls
    through to #~"typedef_base" so typedef methods can use base-type operators.]
  [#*: #+ Added #~"CALL" handling to #~"_check_operation()" so nested calls
    in return arguments are properly type-checked.]


#---: Phase 48c: Missing-return control flow analysis \[DONE\]

The implicit return validation in #~"_check_function_body" catches
functions where the last statement does not produce a value matching
the declared return type. Combined with #~"_last_statement_type"
(which returns #~"_NORETURN" for return/break/continue via
#~"call_kind"), this ensures all non-void functions produce correct
values or emit type errors.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Implicit return type validation: last statement type must match
    declared #~"out" type, or an error is emitted.]
  [#*: #+ #~"_last_statement_type" uses #~"CallKind" enum to detect
    non-completing branches (return, break, continue, error).]


#---: Phase 48d: Eliminate isinstance — field-based dispatch \[DONE\]

Eliminated all 459 #~"isinstance()" calls with field-based dispatch.

#ol:
  [#*: Error made a Node subclass with #~"nodetype = ERROR" and
    #~"is_error = True". Parser Error checks use #~"is_error" + #~"cast()".]
  [#*: AST node dispatch replaced with #~"nodetype" + #~"cast()" across
    parser, typechecker, emitter, prettyprinter, AST hasher.]
  [#*: VFS DEntry dispatch replaced with #~"entrytype" field checks.]
  [#*: ZType checks: #~"TAG_ORIGIN" sentinel replaces #~'"tag"' string,
    #~"is not TAG_ORIGIN" narrows #~"generic_origin". #~"is_ztype"
    field added for polymorphic contexts.]
  [#*: Node base class checks: #~"is_node" field on #~"Node" (True)
    and #~"Token" (False), #~"getattr" dispatch in tree walkers.]
  [#*: Token/Expression: #~"is_expression" field on both classes,
    #~"cast(Token, p)" after guard for type narrowing.]
  [#*: Primitives: #~"type(x) is int/float/bool" replaces
    #~"isinstance".]
  [#*: Containers: #~"type(val) is dict/list" in tree walkers.]
  [#*: Error oplist: #~"getattr(oplist, 'is_error', False)" +
    #~"cast()" for #~"Union\[List, Error\]" returns.]
  [#*: TrackedList: #~"is_tracked_list" field.]


#---: Phase 49a: Type Narrowing (Flow Typing)

Implement compile-time type narrowing for union and variant types via
a TypeState flow-typing system. Narrowing occurs within match arms,
after match arms that diverge (return/break/continue), and on
assignment to a specific subtype. TypeState is intra-function only
and does not cross function call boundaries.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Add TypeState class to ztypes.py (narrow, exclude, merge, lookup).]
  [#*: #+ Thread TypeState through type checker as instance variable.]
  [#*: #+ Modify _resolve_name to consult TypeState before symbol table.]
  [#*: #+ Match arm narrowing: narrow target to subtype within each arm scope.]
  [#*: #+ Post-match narrowing: exclude subtypes from diverging arms.]
  [#*: #+ Else clause: narrow to union minus all explicit case subtypes.]
  [#*: #+ Assignment narrowing: narrow on subtype constructor assignment.]
  [#*: #+ Reassignment: reset narrowing, re-narrow if RHS is subtype.]
  [#*: #+ Dead code detection: error on statements after unreachable TypeState.]
  [#*: #+ Single-subtype collapse: when one subtype remains, type is that subtype.]
  [#*: #+ New example: examples/narrowing.z demonstrating all narrowing patterns.]
  [#*: #+ Tests: within-arm, post-match, assignment, reassignment, nested, loops,
    dead code, function boundary, emitter integration.]
  [#*: #+ Documentation: update spec.pdoc type narrowing section, grammar.pdoc
    match section, and TODO.pdoc to mark narrowing as implemented.]

