#~"doc/roadmap.pdoc", #~"doc/spec.pdoc", #~"doc/grammar.pdoc", #~"doc/TODO.pdoc",
#~"examples/narrowing.z", #~"tests/test_typecheck.py"


#---: Phase 49b: 'is'/'as' Section Semantics \[COMPLETE\]

Enforce and document the semantics of #~"is" and #~"as" sections on objects
(records, classes, unions, variants). Add namespace collision detection,
verify function pointer field replacement, and implement integer constants in
the #~"as" section.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Namespace collision detection: same name in both #~"is" and #~"as" is
    a compile error. Helper function #~"_check_is_as_name_collision" added to
    #~"ztypecheck.py", called from all four #~"_resolve_*_type" methods. Also
    checks field-vs-function and item-vs-item cross-section collisions.]
  [#*: #+ Duplicate definition tests: parser already catches duplicate #~"is"
    clause, duplicate #~"as" clause, and duplicate item names within a body.
    Added test coverage for all cases.]
  [#*: #+ Function pointer replacement: functions defined in #~"is" section are
    stored as per-instance function pointer fields. These can be replaced on
    both record and class instances via #~"=" reassignment. Already worked end
    to end; added test coverage and example demonstrating replacement.]
  [#*: #+ Integer constants in #~"as" section: numeric literals in #~"as" are
    now type-checked and emitted as #~"static const" in the generated C code.
    Constants are accessed via #~"TypeName.const_name" and are immutable
    (reassignment is a compile error).]
  [#*: #+ Updated #~"examples/specs.z" with function pointer replacement and
    static constant demonstrations.]
  [#*: #+ Updated #~"doc/spec.pdoc" with new section documenting #~"is" and
    #~"as" section semantics.]

