#---: Phase 49c: Take in Match Arms \[COMPLETE\]

Allow #~".take" on the match subject inside arm bodies for ownership
transfer. Remove the unnecessary EXCLUSIVE lock from match (arms are
mutually exclusive, subject evaluated once). Implement deferred
invalidation so each arm sees the original subject state.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Remove EXCLUSIVE lock from match subjects (not needed, unlike
    #~"for" and function calls where locking prevents aliasing/mutation
    during re-evaluation).]
  [#*: #+ Track take-in-arms: if the subject is taken in any arm, restore
    it for subsequent arms so each arm sees the original ownership state.]
  [#*: #+ Post-match invalidation: if any arm takes the subject, invalidate
    it after the match. Using it subsequently is a compile error.]
  [#*: #+ Post-match cleanup in emitter: after the switch/if-else, emit a
    NULL-check destroy for the subject if it was taken in any arm.]
  [#*: #+ Fix taken-variable detection in dotted path fallback resolution
    (added #~"_taken" check in regular dotted path resolution path).]
  [#*: #+ Tests: type checker (5 tests) and emitter (3 tests including
    ASan memory leak check).]
  [#*: #+ Documentation: updated #~"ownership.pdoc" (match no-lock rationale,
    take-in-arms semantics), #~"spec.pdoc" (match section), and roadmap.]

