#---: Phase 49d: 'as' Section — Expanded Static Namespace \[COMPLETE\]

Expand the #~"as" section to accept a wider range of static items beyond
integer constants: float constants, computed constant expressions, and
references to externally-defined definitions.

#ol:
  [#*: #+ Float constants: #~"as { pi: 3.14 }" — extend type checker and
    emitter to accept float values alongside integers.]
  [#*: #+ References to existing definitions: #~"as { limit: max_size }" —
    propagate #~"const_value" from referenced unit-level definitions.]
  [#*: #+ Computed constant expressions: #~"as { max: 2 * 1024 }" — upgrade
    parser to accept operations in object bodies, evaluate via constant
    folding.]
  [#*: #+ Updated #~"_fold_binop" to accept float operands.]
  [#*: #+ Updated AST #~"const_value" and ZType #~"const_value" to accept
    float values.]
  [#*: #+ String constants: #~"as { name: \"hello\" }" — emitted as
    #~"ZSTR_STATIC" with #~"#define" alias. Static strings are immutable
    and skip #~"zstr_free" (static flag in size field). Interpolated strings
    are rejected at compile time.]
  [#*: #_ Inline definitions (data, records) in #~"as" — deferred (references
    to external definitions cover the common cases).]

